The agent A provided the following violation scenario:Calling strlen(c->rq.method) when c->rq.method may not be null-terminated. If c->rq.http_mthd == MHD_HTTP_MTHD_OTHER the code calls strlen(c->rq.method) without any bounded check. If the method buffer is not NUL-terminated within its allocated bounds, strlen will read beyond the object, violating Rule 21.17.
</scenario>
